<DOC><DOCNO> SJMN91-06281023 </DOCNO><ACCESS> 06281023 </ACCESS><DESCRIPT>  WASHINGTON; COLLEGE; EDUCATION; MONEY; CHARITY; COMPUTER; SOFTWARE; COMPANY;OFFICIAL; MEDICAL; GENETIC; TECHNOLOGY  </DESCRIPT><LEADPARA>  Microsoft Corp. Chairman Bill Gates, the second-richest man in the UnitedStates, shared some of his wealth today by donating $12 million to theUniversity of Washington.;   The gift will be used to create a department ofmolecular biotechnology at the college's medical school and to hire notedimmunologist Leroy Hood of the California Institute of Technology as thedepartment's first chairman.  </LEADPARA><SECTION>  Business  </SECTION><HEADLINE>  GATES GIVES $12 MILLION TO SCHOOL  </HEADLINE><TEXT>     Gates' donation also will be used to set up an intellectual venture capitalfund that will provide seed money for university scientists in molecularbiotechnology research.;   Molecular biotechnology is the study of DNA andother major building blocks of life. Scientists are researching ways to modifythese building blocks to identify and treat diseases and other medicalproblems.;   Gates' donation is the largest ever to the university, eclipsingthe $11 million donated three years ago by Microsoft co-founder Paul Allen.;  Gates told a news conference that biotechnology is one of his chief interestsin addition to computers. Gates has invested in a small biotech company, ICOSCorp. of Seattle, but he said that company won't be directly involved with theuniversity.;   Gates, 35, did not attend the University of Washington, but hismother, Mary Gates, is a regent of the university and a member of the board ofits medical center.;   The most recent issue of Forbes magazine lists Gates asthe second-richest man in America, with an estimated worth of $4.8 billion --a fortune he made as Microsoft became the world's biggest maker of computersoftware.  </TEXT><BYLINE>  Associated Press  </BYLINE><COUNTRY>  USA  </COUNTRY><CITY>  Seattle  </CITY><EDITION>  Stock Final  </EDITION><CODE>  SJ  </CODE><NAME>  San Jose Mercury News  </NAME><PUBDATE>   911007  </PUBDATE> <DAY>  Monday  </DAY><MONTH>  October  </MONTH><PG.COL>  9D  </PG.COL><PUBYEAR>  1991  </PUBYEAR><REGION>  WEST  </REGION><STATE>  CA  </STATE><WORD.CT>  252  </WORD.CT><DATELINE>  Monday, October 7, 199100281023,SJ1  </DATELINE><COPYRGHT>  Copyright 1991, San Jose Mercury News  </COPYRGHT><LIMLEN>  1  </LIMLEN><LANGUAGE>  ENG  </LANGUAGE></DOC>